####################### Ceph Preconfig UEFI ########################

This is a WIP kickstart file for setting up a Rocky 9 host using UEFI boot mode. 
What it currently does:
-Automatically grabs first two detected drives to use as boot drives.
-Provisions them with RAID1 partitions for /boot/efi and /.
-Installs 45drives and Cephadm packages (uses latest version of Squid).
-Performs steps detailed in our Rocky9-Ceph-Preconfig.sh script.

IN TESTING:
-Includes function that fails the execution of the kickstart file if one of the detected drives has a Ceph partition.
Note that the Kickstart installer will not display a specialized error message when it fails as a result of this function. Further investigation is required to find a workaround.

HOW TO USE:
-Consult the guide on how to install on Rocky 9 (UEFI Mode) here: http://192.168.1.91/doku45/doku.php?id=service:serv-ts-_testing_headless_rocky_install:network
